{
  "texts": [
    "Homogeneous agents have identical thresholds, while heterogeneous agents differ in their thresholds.",
    "For agents with very high thresholds, very few papers will meet that bar for a substantive citation, so more of the reference list will be composed of rhetorical citations.",
    "In this way, thresholds help determine the composition of the reference list, even when its overall length is fixed.",
    "• Quality and fit: A paper i's underlying quality is represented by q i and distributed as Beta (1,6) in the paper population.",
    "Underlying quality does not have an index j because it is assumed to be identical for all agents."
  ]
}